{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17643269","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17643269"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:52:42+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:52:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17995"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17995","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17995"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.95,0,0,0,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10709"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79175"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10709","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10709"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17995"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64527"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"10053"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24931"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24933"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79175","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79175"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following describes a potential benefit of intermittent fasting?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Improved HbA1c levels","Increased muscle mass","Higher blood pressure","Decreased bone density","Increased appetite"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImproved HbA1c levels\u003C/strong\u003E are a potential benefit of intermittent fasting. This dietary approach can lead to better glycaemic control by improving insulin sensitivity and reducing blood glucose levels, which is beneficial for individuals with type 2 diabetes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased muscle mass\u003C/strong\u003E is not associated with intermittent fasting. While fasting can help with weight loss, maintaining or increasing muscle mass usually requires resistance training and adequate protein intake.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHigher blood pressure\u003C/strong\u003E is not a benefit of intermittent fasting. Some studies suggest that intermittent fasting may help lower blood pressure as part of overall cardiovascular health improvements.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased bone density\u003C/strong\u003E is not a known effect of intermittent fasting. Bone health is more closely related to factors such as calcium and vitamin D intake, physical activity, and hormonal balance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased appetite\u003C/strong\u003E is not a benefit of intermittent fasting. While some individuals may experience increased hunger initially, many find that their appetite stabilises over time as they adjust to the fasting regimen.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Intermittent fasting can lead to improved glycaemic control, including better HbA1c levels.","Intermittent fasting may contribute to weight loss and improved metabolic health.","Intermittent fasting can have positive effects on insulin sensitivity."],"references":["Borgundvaag E, Mak J, Kramer CK. Metabolic Impact of Intermittent Fasting in Patients With Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus: A Systematic Review and Meta-analysis of Interventional Studies. J Clin Endocrinol Metab. 2021 Mar 8;106(3):902-911. doi: 10.1210/clinem/dgaa926. PMID: 33319233.","Saeed M, Ali M, Zehra T, Haider Zaidi SA, Tariq R. Intermittent Fasting: A User-Friendly Method for Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus. Cureus. 2021 Nov 8;13(11):e19348. doi: 10.7759/cureus.19348. PMID: 34909309; PMCID: PMC8653959.","Nowosad K, Sujka M. Effect of Various Types of Intermittent Fasting (IF) on Weight Loss and Improvement of Diabetic Parameters in Human. Curr Nutr Rep. 2021 Jun;10(2):146-154. doi: 10.1007/s13668-021-00353-5. Epub 2021 Apr 7. PMID: 33826120; PMCID: PMC8102292.","Patterson RE, Sears DD. Metabolic Effects of Intermittent Fasting. Annu Rev Nutr. 2017 Aug 21;37:371-393. doi: 10.1146/annurev-nutr-071816-064634. Epub 2017 Jul 17. PMID: 28715993."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64527"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17995"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64527","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64527"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-13T16:15:24+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-13T16:15:55+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10709"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79175"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving inf